\f0 \cf2 //Adapt any of the instruments provided in the code examples to produce single "cloud" of granular events when triggered by a GUI button, or by a keyboard event. The trigger will start a Routine that changes arguments in the instrument over time. It should have a discrete start and end, and be retriggerable, so that multiple starts produce new clouds that overlap. Play your instrument using your own samples and record a performance. (a single cloud that has a beginning and an end create a routine that "moves the GUI controls")}